1
00:00:00,164 --> 00:00:01,989
Sparkling Wine Is In Its Prime.

2
00:00:01,989 --> 00:00:04,652
Here Are Five Bottles To Savor.

3
00:00:04,652 --> 00:00:17,458
New varieties beyond traditional Champagnes and Proseccos are inviting drinkers to reconsider bubbles.

4
00:00:17,458 --> 00:00:24,106
Some might associate sparkling wine mostly with special occasions, like wedding toasts or New Year's Eve.

5
00:00:24,106 --> 00:00:29,104
Others may think of their favorite spritz—whether Aperol, Campari or Hugo.

6
00:00:29,104 --> 00:00:41,476
But recently, a proliferation of sparkling wines beyond the usual Champagnes, Cavas, Crémants and Proseccos has burnished the beverage's reputation as one to enjoy on its own, on any day of the year.

7
00:00:41,476 --> 00:00:48,436
"I know people who are not in the industry that drink bubbles every day," said Tonya Pitts, a sommelier in San Francisco. "

8
00:00:48,436 --> 00:00:51,893
"It's so accessible now and people are drinking more of it." "

9
00:00:51,893 --> 00:01:02,630
As consumption of wine and spirits writ large has been in steady decline, sparkling wine has maintained, well, its sparkle—outperforming other categories with carbonated verve.

10
00:01:02,630 --> 00:01:15,141
The global sparkling wine market has continued to grow, reaching nearly $50 billion in 2025, according to analysis from Maximize Market Research, a firm that tracks industry trends.

11
00:01:15,141 --> 00:01:21,809
Its projections show the sparkling wine market expanding to about $69 billion by 2032.

12
00:01:21,809 --> 00:01:29,235
The drink's evolution has included more sparkling wines made with red wine grapes, such as Pinot Noir and Cabernet Franc.

13
00:01:29,235 --> 00:01:41,245
"If the varietal can be grown and produced to have enough acidity on its own without having to add acidity to change the structure of your end product, it can be used to produce sparkling wine," Pitts explained.&nbsp;

14
00:01:41,245 --> 00:01:48,617
More sparkling wines are now also sold at stores not typically associated with specialty beverages, like Aldi and Costco.

15
00:01:48,617 --> 00:01:52,865
With people drinking less, many are opting for bottles that feel more special—

16
00:01:52,865 --> 00:01:55,365
whether from a small producer, a sustainable vineyard or, increasingly, a category long associated with celebration and quality.

